==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mulligrubs
<hw>Mul"li*grubs</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Prov. E.
<ets>mull</ets> to squeeze, pull about, <ets>mulling</ets> numb or
dull.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A griping of the intestines; colic.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whose dog lies sick of the <qex>mulligrubs</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, sullenness; the sulks.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mullingong</ent>⟦br⟧
